1
00:01:10,752 --> 00:01:12,431
=Those Days=

2
00:01:12,431 --> 00:01:14,800
(Adapted from iceread.com novel
"You Xi" by Qingyang Wanxi)

3
00:01:14,980 --> 00:01:18,130
=Episode 36=

4
00:01:19,119 --> 00:01:19,919
Ni, take a look.

5
00:01:20,960 --> 00:01:22,600
What do you think of our new

6
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:23,559
renovation style?

7
00:01:29,479 --> 00:01:30,839
Please, this way.

8
00:01:31,080 --> 00:01:31,640
Okay.

9
00:01:33,160 --> 00:01:33,640
Mr. Zhao.

10
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:34,160
Mingzhu.

11
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:37,720
These two guests

12
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:38,640
are my friends.

13
00:01:38,839 --> 00:01:40,800
Make sure you take good care of them.

14
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:43,080
- Hello, I'm Shen Mingzhu.

15
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:43,640
Hi.

16
00:01:44,039 --> 00:01:44,759
These days,

17
00:01:44,759 --> 00:01:45,919
all our restaurant operations

18
00:01:45,919 --> 00:01:47,279
are handled by Shen Mingzhu.

19
00:01:47,399 --> 00:01:49,679
So if you need anything,

20
00:01:49,679 --> 00:01:51,170
you can talk to Shen Mingzhu directly.

21
00:01:51,180 --> 00:01:52,710
She'll explain
and coordinate everything.

22
00:01:52,720 --> 00:01:53,399
Great.

23
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:55,160
Why don't you guys discuss it?

24
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:56,199
I'll get out of your hair.

25
00:01:56,199 --> 00:01:57,119
Thanks, Mr. Zhao.

26
00:01:57,119 --> 00:01:57,679
No problem.

27
00:01:57,880 --> 00:01:58,279
Thanks.

28
00:01:58,279 --> 00:01:59,360
Go ahead. It's fine.

29
00:02:00,199 --> 00:02:00,839
Ms. Shen,

30
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:02,679
this banquet hall must've had

31
00:02:02,679 --> 00:02:04,039
a lot of thought put into it.

32
00:02:04,199 --> 00:02:05,080
How much did it cost?

33
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:07,759
The renovation cost
about a hundred grand.

34
00:02:08,640 --> 00:02:09,719
A hundred thousand?

35
00:02:09,999 --> 00:02:11,279
And you got it looking like this?

36
00:02:12,480 --> 00:02:13,999
Miss Shen, you're seriously impressive.

37
00:02:14,220 --> 00:02:15,279
No need for the formality.

38
00:02:15,279 --> 00:02:16,320
Just call me Mingzhu.

39
00:02:16,559 --> 00:02:18,040
Since you're Mr. Zhao's friends,

40
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:19,240
you're my friends too.

41
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:21,399
I'll make sure
you're well taken care of.

42
00:02:21,599 --> 00:02:23,640
So, how may I help you?

43
00:02:25,599 --> 00:02:27,200
We want to book an engagement banquet.

44
00:02:27,599 --> 00:02:28,439
Yes, for the wedding.

45
00:02:29,559 --> 00:02:30,599
Let's sit down and talk.

46
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:31,439
Okay.

47
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:39,879
Then let me congratulate you in advance.

48
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:41,200
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

49
00:02:41,599 --> 00:02:43,960
When are you planning to get married?

50
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:47,080
Probably this fall.

51
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,599
The most comfortable season of the year.

52
00:02:48,599 --> 00:02:49,800
Great choice.

53
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:51,080
Clear skies, cool weather.

54
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,559
Fall is perfect for weddings.

55
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:53,520
By then,

56
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:55,119
our banquet hall will already be open.

57
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:57,119
If you decide to hold it here,

58
00:02:57,119 --> 00:02:57,999
we're confident

59
00:02:57,999 --> 00:02:59,279
we can give you

60
00:02:59,279 --> 00:03:00,679
a truly memorable wedding.

61
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:02,839
As for the Nanxi Hotel,

62
00:03:02,839 --> 00:03:04,320
it's always had good taste.

63
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:05,640
But it's been around a long time,

64
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:06,750
it doesn't feel new anymore.

65
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:08,119
So now, do you have

66
00:03:08,119 --> 00:03:09,559
any special recommendations?

67
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:12,119
Nanxi Hotel does have a long history.

68
00:03:12,320 --> 00:03:13,960
But that's actually our charm.

69
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:14,920
We've hosted

70
00:03:14,920 --> 00:03:16,960
a lot of traditional,
vintage-style weddings here.

71
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:18,320
And after the renovation,

72
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:19,679
we've added a wide range

73
00:03:19,679 --> 00:03:22,119
of modern, stylish wedding themes

74
00:03:22,119 --> 00:03:23,200
for people to choose from.

75
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:26,119
We've also done
a lot of successful events recently.

76
00:03:26,119 --> 00:03:27,480
Our clients were very happy.

77
00:03:27,839 --> 00:03:28,879
I have some slides here.

78
00:03:28,879 --> 00:03:29,920
You can take a look.

79
00:03:32,839 --> 00:03:33,960
This one is French style.

80
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:39,240
Have a nice day.

81
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:39,679
Okay.

82
00:03:39,679 --> 00:03:40,760
- Thanks for your help.
- Bye.

83
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:41,320
Bye.

84
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:43,960
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

85
00:03:53,559 --> 00:03:54,200
Mingzhu.

86
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:54,760
Mom.

87
00:03:55,060 --> 00:03:55,920
What brings you here?

88
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:58,080
I brought you food.

89
00:03:58,399 --> 00:03:59,800
You've all been so busy lately.

90
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:00,960
You haven't been eating well.

91
00:04:02,719 --> 00:04:03,999
You didn't have to make a trip.

92
00:04:04,159 --> 00:04:05,520
Of course I did.

93
00:04:08,439 --> 00:04:09,320
Mingzhu.

94
00:04:09,559 --> 00:04:12,559
I said something
I shouldn't have yesterday.

95
00:04:13,119 --> 00:04:14,240
I owe you an apology.

96
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:15,240
What did you say?

97
00:04:16,060 --> 00:04:18,640
I shouldn't have said you were living
under someone else's roof.

98
00:04:18,640 --> 00:04:20,000
I was wrong. I'm sorry.

99
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,239
Mom, we're family.

100
00:04:21,359 --> 00:04:22,520
Don't take it to heart.

101
00:04:28,159 --> 00:04:28,799
Mingzhu.

102
00:04:30,039 --> 00:04:32,719
There's actually something else
I want to talk to you about.

103
00:04:34,279 --> 00:04:34,960
Go ahead.

104
00:04:37,479 --> 00:04:38,159
Meiqi.

105
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:39,760
I saw your mom just now.

106
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:42,520
She's over there talking to Mingzhu.

107
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:44,799
Thanks, I got it.

108
00:04:47,220 --> 00:04:48,120
Let me put it this way.

109
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:48,919
I came here today

110
00:04:48,919 --> 00:04:50,719
because I want to officially invite you

111
00:04:50,719 --> 00:04:52,320
to join me and Meiqi.

112
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:55,399
The three of us together,
bringing the factory back to life.

113
00:04:58,599 --> 00:05:00,399
This is really sudden.

114
00:05:01,359 --> 00:05:02,839
I need some time to think about it.

115
00:05:02,839 --> 00:05:04,239
Trust me, Mingzhu.

116
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,919
As long as
we get the factory running again,

117
00:05:05,919 --> 00:05:07,919
all the money you put in at the start

118
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:09,120
will be worth it.

119
00:05:09,839 --> 00:05:11,039
We can afford to lose.

120
00:05:11,839 --> 00:05:13,320
I can't afford to lose anymore.

121
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:14,239
Mom.

122
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:16,080
Meiqi.

123
00:05:16,479 --> 00:05:17,479
What brings you here?

124
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:20,159
I made some food.

125
00:05:20,159 --> 00:05:21,880
I brought it for you and Mingzhu.

126
00:05:22,399 --> 00:05:23,680
You can join her.

127
00:05:24,239 --> 00:05:24,799
Okay.

128
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:25,640
Alright.

129
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:26,799
Go on, go get back to work.

130
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:28,159
Okay, we're heading out.

131
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,719
Go, go, go.

132
00:05:31,159 --> 00:05:32,000
What did Mom say?

133
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:33,640
Mingzhu.

134
00:05:37,599 --> 00:05:38,760
Go eat. Go on.

135
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:05,599
Making me wait again?

136
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:08,760
My little Mingzhu is upset now.

137
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:10,479
I'll buy you a drink later, okay?

138
00:06:15,479 --> 00:06:16,239
Tell me why

139
00:06:16,239 --> 00:06:18,520
I always have to
be the one making choices.

140
00:06:19,279 --> 00:06:21,359
I already handled everything.

141
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:23,520
But no one ever asks what I think.

142
00:06:23,799 --> 00:06:25,799
No one ever asks
if I even want to do it.

143
00:06:26,599 --> 00:06:27,960
I care. I really care.

144
00:06:27,960 --> 00:06:30,039
Then tell me this,
do you want to do it or not?

145
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:32,320
See?

146
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:33,950
I asked, and you still won't say.

147
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:35,919
If I say it out loud,

148
00:06:36,359 --> 00:06:37,839
it makes things harder for everyone.

149
00:06:38,839 --> 00:06:39,520
True.

150
00:06:40,159 --> 00:06:41,520
You've always been the one

151
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:42,440
who swallows it.

152
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:44,880
For everything else, fine,

153
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:46,330
I don't have any selfish intentions.

154
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:48,200
But the restaurant

155
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:50,080
is not my own selfish wish.

156
00:06:50,479 --> 00:06:51,120
Think about it.

157
00:06:51,239 --> 00:06:53,039
Meiqi and Jianqi's mom are jobless.

158
00:06:53,039 --> 00:06:54,440
How were they supposed to live?

159
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:56,239
And look where we ended up.

160
00:06:58,239 --> 00:07:00,440
I just wanted a simple life,

161
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:01,799
to get through this rough patch.

162
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:03,479
I never wanted to be

163
00:07:03,479 --> 00:07:04,799
some hero saving everyone

164
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:06,000
or the protagonist.

165
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:08,839
I just want to hold on
to whatever small happiness I can.

166
00:07:09,279 --> 00:07:11,440
Why does it never go the way I hoped?

167
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,960
I honestly used up so much strength

168
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:16,159
just to make it this far.

169
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:23,359
Listen to me.

170
00:07:24,279 --> 00:07:25,960
You've already done more than enough.

171
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:27,000
Really.

172
00:07:27,359 --> 00:07:29,599
You've been amazing since we were kids.

173
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:32,520
You just think
about everyone else too much.

174
00:07:33,399 --> 00:07:36,159
With this, stop worrying
about what other people think

175
00:07:36,159 --> 00:07:37,080
or their opinions.

176
00:07:37,479 --> 00:07:38,320
Just ask yourself

177
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:39,200
if you want to do it.

178
00:07:41,490 --> 00:07:42,159
Think about it.

179
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:59,399
I'm guessing you want
an iced Coke right now.

180
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:03,120
Can pregnant women drink iced Coke?

181
00:08:03,239 --> 00:08:04,919
Of course you can. Why not?

182
00:08:05,279 --> 00:08:06,080
I'm the expert.

183
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:07,479
If I say you can, you can.

184
00:08:07,479 --> 00:08:08,839
What, are you carrying a demon

185
00:08:08,839 --> 00:08:10,260
that won't even
let you have a Coke?

186
00:08:12,279 --> 00:08:13,279
So many of my boundaries

187
00:08:13,279 --> 00:08:14,680
get broken because of you.

188
00:08:15,399 --> 00:08:16,520
Come on, don't exaggerate.

189
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:17,560
It's just a Coke.

190
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:24,000
So good.

191
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:24,599
So good!

192
00:08:39,160 --> 00:08:42,359
Don't buy more eggs
if the ones at home aren't finished.

193
00:08:42,680 --> 00:08:43,759
I didn't buy them.

194
00:08:43,759 --> 00:08:45,719
Zhang Hao bought them.
They were on sale.

195
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:48,519
He just loves buying things on sale.

196
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:50,479
I'm not coming home for lunch.

197
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:52,560
Where are you going?

198
00:08:52,719 --> 00:08:53,359
Got stuff to do.

199
00:08:54,759 --> 00:08:57,320
Always busy running around
doing who-knows-what.

200
00:08:57,519 --> 00:08:58,160
Seriously.

201
00:09:02,119 --> 00:09:02,719
Shen.

202
00:09:03,119 --> 00:09:04,200
I'm heading out for a bit.

203
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:04,879
Where you going?

204
00:09:05,119 --> 00:09:05,999
I'll be right back.

205
00:09:07,550 --> 00:09:09,239
Bring back some cilantro if you see any.

206
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:16,920
- Grocery run.
- Hello.

207
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:17,519
Heading out.

208
00:09:19,839 --> 00:09:20,639
Yes, indeed.

209
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:21,800
Yeah.

210
00:09:22,599 --> 00:09:24,440
Xu, where are you off to?

211
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:29,359
Going to see someone.

212
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:35,680
Xiu'e.

213
00:09:35,879 --> 00:09:36,479
Heading out?

214
00:09:46,239 --> 00:09:47,080
Cleaning veggies?

215
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:50,479
Just got back.

216
00:09:50,479 --> 00:09:51,759
Yeah, the fruit is cheap today.

217
00:09:51,759 --> 00:09:52,639
Want one?

218
00:09:52,639 --> 00:09:53,200
I'm good.

219
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:54,239
Your veggies look fresh.

220
00:09:54,239 --> 00:09:54,839
Yep.

221
00:09:54,839 --> 00:09:56,080
The soybeans are in season.

222
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,550
- Rare to see you grocery shopping.
- True enough.

223
00:09:58,239 --> 00:09:58,879
Miss.

224
00:09:58,879 --> 00:10:00,239
I'm trying to find someone.

225
00:10:00,359 --> 00:10:03,119
Her surname is Yu. Yu Jingxiang.

226
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:38,800
I'm sorry.

227
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:40,359
Please forgive me.

228
00:10:44,359 --> 00:10:45,040
Xiu'e.

229
00:10:48,759 --> 00:10:49,359
You...

230
00:10:51,239 --> 00:10:53,639
What are you doing here?

231
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:00,800
Mr. Shen.

232
00:11:03,999 --> 00:11:05,680
Your mom hasn't changed one bit.

233
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:07,879
Right.

234
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:19,960
You're keeping the flowers really well.

235
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:21,680
Yeah. I grew them.

236
00:11:26,879 --> 00:11:27,759
So, well...

237
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:36,400
I know that girl came by

238
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:38,800
to apologize to you for me.

239
00:11:39,519 --> 00:11:40,519
And Shen keeps saying

240
00:11:40,519 --> 00:11:42,119
I didn't handle the situation right.

241
00:11:42,119 --> 00:11:42,680
I just...

242
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:47,879
Yes, the note existed.

243
00:11:52,239 --> 00:11:54,180
This was something I…

244
00:11:54,190 --> 00:11:55,239
I should've told you myself

245
00:11:55,239 --> 00:11:56,839
instead of letting Mingzhu apologize for me.

246
00:11:56,839 --> 00:11:57,440
Wait.

247
00:11:57,810 --> 00:11:59,359
Saying it out loud makes me feel better.

248
00:11:59,359 --> 00:12:00,060
Really, it does.

249
00:12:00,070 --> 00:12:01,560
I've had it bottled up for years.

250
00:12:01,560 --> 00:12:02,599
I felt terrible too.

251
00:12:03,359 --> 00:12:03,999
Xiu'e.

252
00:12:04,999 --> 00:12:08,160
Honestly, you raised Mingzhu
when she was a tiny little girl.

253
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:10,359
You've raised her well.

254
00:12:11,040 --> 00:12:12,280
All your kindness...

255
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:12,839
I've...

256
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:15,519
I've felt them.

257
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:18,879
Really. I mean that.

258
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:20,040
Mr. Shen.

259
00:12:20,920 --> 00:12:23,080
That day was totally my fault.

260
00:12:23,519 --> 00:12:24,879
It was supposed to be wonderful,

261
00:12:25,340 --> 00:12:26,680
and I somehow managed to ruin it.

262
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:28,040
I made everyone awkward.

263
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:32,879
It's because of this.

264
00:12:33,560 --> 00:12:35,280
I drank too much that day.

265
00:12:35,479 --> 00:12:37,479
And then I pulled that thing out.

266
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:38,920
I promise you,

267
00:12:39,359 --> 00:12:40,200
from now on,

268
00:12:40,479 --> 00:12:42,839
it has nothing to do with us.

269
00:12:43,479 --> 00:12:44,160
It's void.

270
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:47,519
How could it not matter?

271
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:48,999
You don't believe me?

272
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:56,920
What are you doing?

273
00:12:57,239 --> 00:12:58,800
Burning it. Turning the page.

274
00:13:00,119 --> 00:13:01,320
Hold on, you can't...

275
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:02,280
I'm getting rid of it.

276
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:03,320
This has to go away.

277
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,080
See?

278
00:13:09,719 --> 00:13:10,320
Look.

279
00:13:14,359 --> 00:13:15,320
Where's the note?

280
00:13:17,479 --> 00:13:18,119
It's gone.

281
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:21,599
That note never existed
in this world anymore.

282
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:24,200
Let's not bring it up again. It's done.

283
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:26,400
Honestly, it should've been
over a long time ago.

284
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:27,479
I'm just too stubborn,

285
00:13:27,479 --> 00:13:28,080
you know?

286
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:29,479
But when I think about it,

287
00:13:29,920 --> 00:13:31,759
it's great for a kid to have two moms.

288
00:13:31,759 --> 00:13:32,280
It is.

289
00:13:32,599 --> 00:13:34,759
If one of us ever gets sick,

290
00:13:34,759 --> 00:13:36,680
or we have to
go visit relatives somewhere,

291
00:13:36,680 --> 00:13:38,060
there's someone there to help out.

292
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:38,879
Exactly.

293
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:40,519
Mingzhu told me

294
00:13:40,519 --> 00:13:42,320
that she's already put this behind her.

295
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:43,280
Right.

296
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:44,560
So don't keep holding it inside.

297
00:13:44,560 --> 00:13:46,560
We'll leave it in the past.

298
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:47,359
Right?

299
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:47,960
Right.

300
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:48,879
From now on,

301
00:13:49,639 --> 00:13:52,639
we're one family.

302
00:13:52,639 --> 00:13:53,920
But let me tell you,

303
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:56,639
don't celebrate just yet.

304
00:13:56,719 --> 00:13:58,160
You're not allowed to favor your son.

305
00:13:58,160 --> 00:13:58,560
Okay.

306
00:13:58,560 --> 00:14:00,359
If you mistreat our Mingzhu,

307
00:14:00,359 --> 00:14:01,879
I won't be as polite next time.

308
00:14:02,519 --> 00:14:03,879
Okay, okay.

309
00:14:03,879 --> 00:14:04,879
Don't worry.

310
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:07,639
Alright, I should go.

311
00:14:07,879 --> 00:14:08,999
I have work at the shop.

312
00:14:08,999 --> 00:14:09,999
I'll head out.

313
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:10,719
Okay.

314
00:14:10,719 --> 00:14:12,239
Find some time to drop by.

315
00:14:12,239 --> 00:14:12,759
Okay.

316
00:14:12,759 --> 00:14:13,280
Alright then.

317
00:14:13,519 --> 00:14:14,160
I'm off.

318
00:14:14,160 --> 00:14:16,120
- I can see myself out.
-  I'm not keeping you.

319
00:14:30,359 --> 00:14:31,040
Mom.

320
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:33,119
Mom.

321
00:14:34,999 --> 00:14:36,080
It all worked out.

322
00:14:43,759 --> 00:14:45,200
That's a lot of silk.

323
00:14:46,839 --> 00:14:48,040
At this year's price,

324
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:49,479
how much would this be worth?

325
00:14:50,599 --> 00:14:51,999
At least three million.

326
00:14:52,479 --> 00:14:53,599
Three million?

327
00:14:53,599 --> 00:14:54,440
Three million.

328
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:56,560
It's the soft gold of fabrics.

329
00:14:57,320 --> 00:14:58,680
The price must've multiplied

330
00:14:58,999 --> 00:14:59,999
since I was a kid.

331
00:15:00,879 --> 00:15:01,920
More than a few.

332
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:03,800
Mingzhu,

333
00:15:04,519 --> 00:15:05,320
look at this.

334
00:15:05,759 --> 00:15:06,839
When Jianqi was little,

335
00:15:06,839 --> 00:15:09,119
he used to run around here playing.

336
00:15:09,119 --> 00:15:10,160
He was such a handful.

337
00:15:10,839 --> 00:15:12,160
But he had his good moments too.

338
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:14,280
When I had Meiqi,

339
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:16,359
he even helped me rock her to sleep.

340
00:15:17,479 --> 00:15:18,759
I don't even remember that.

341
00:15:18,999 --> 00:15:19,800
You were tiny.

342
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:21,200
How would you remember?

343
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:24,360
You were way more
of a troublemaker than your brother,

344
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:25,719
but also smarter.

345
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:26,920
Listen.

346
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:28,359
Just from what's woven on this,

347
00:15:28,359 --> 00:15:29,560
she can tell with a touch

348
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:31,320
what the fabric is like.

349
00:15:31,999 --> 00:15:33,759
And she's great at numbers.

350
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:36,239
She was faster than a calculator.

351
00:15:36,599 --> 00:15:38,440
In that, she's better than Jianqi.

352
00:15:47,599 --> 00:15:48,160
Meiqi.

353
00:15:50,160 --> 00:15:51,440
This is meant to be.

354
00:15:52,519 --> 00:15:54,239
You should go after what you want to do.

355
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:56,560
Mingzhu...

356
00:15:57,479 --> 00:15:59,160
Knowing what you want

357
00:15:59,839 --> 00:16:01,359
is how you figure out where to go next.

358
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:04,119
What about you?

359
00:16:06,719 --> 00:16:07,599
I will too.

360
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:25,839
Meiqi.

361
00:16:26,239 --> 00:16:27,800
Mingzhu, come quick, come look.

362
00:16:28,560 --> 00:16:30,200
It's still here.

363
00:16:32,479 --> 00:16:33,400
What is this?

364
00:16:35,639 --> 00:16:37,759
These are all Jianqi's treasures.

365
00:16:37,759 --> 00:16:38,680
See?

366
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:39,680
His treasures.

367
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:42,040
His marbles.

368
00:16:42,160 --> 00:16:42,800
And this.

369
00:16:43,519 --> 00:16:46,519
I was too busy when he was little.

370
00:16:47,400 --> 00:16:48,759
Jianqi kept pestering me

371
00:16:48,759 --> 00:16:49,839
to play with him.

372
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:52,359
So I threaded all the thimbles together,

373
00:16:52,359 --> 00:16:53,200
tied them in knots,

374
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:54,080
and I told him

375
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:55,680
to open them up.

376
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,680
I told him I'd play with him

377
00:16:57,680 --> 00:16:59,239
if he could untie the knots.

378
00:17:05,270 --> 00:17:06,239
The knots were intact.

379
00:17:08,559 --> 00:17:09,920
It's still here.

380
00:17:12,559 --> 00:17:13,239
Mom.

381
00:17:13,999 --> 00:17:15,400
Can I take a look?

382
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:24,120
Meiqi.

383
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:35,719
Baby.

384
00:17:37,079 --> 00:17:38,760
You will have to
untie them for your dad.

385
00:17:42,759 --> 00:17:44,239
You're quick

386
00:17:44,239 --> 00:17:45,120
at everything,

387
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:46,640
except homework.

388
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:49,239
Mom, is dinner ready?

389
00:17:49,239 --> 00:17:50,880
Dad should be telling me to eat by now.

390
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:51,479
Jiao.

391
00:17:51,479 --> 00:17:53,120
Dinner is ready!

392
00:17:53,279 --> 00:17:54,400
Seriously, you two?

393
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:56,479
Hurry up and eat.

394
00:17:56,999 --> 00:17:59,110
Sitting there any longer
won't get her the answers.

395
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:00,440
Mom is here.

396
00:18:01,239 --> 00:18:02,079
Hello, Grandma.

397
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:03,440
Mom, have you eaten?

398
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:04,759
I haven't.

399
00:18:05,759 --> 00:18:06,640
Mom, join us.

400
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:07,440
Let me through.

401
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:08,400
I need to get through.

402
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:09,840
Come on.

403
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:11,680
Perfect timing.

404
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:12,410
Let me carry that.

405
00:18:12,799 --> 00:18:13,880
I bought some groceries.

406
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:14,759
Take a seat.

407
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:17,640
I'll do it myself.

408
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:18,640
- It's alright.
- Sit.

409
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:19,960
I'll wash my hands first.

410
00:18:20,559 --> 00:18:21,440
Just leave them here.

411
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:34,559
I made a few dishes.

412
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:36,200
Let's eat.

413
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:38,759
About the baby's extra finger...

414
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:42,440
Have you looked into it more?

415
00:18:48,519 --> 00:18:49,160
Mom.

416
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:50,600
Let's eat first.

417
00:18:53,239 --> 00:18:54,759
You left in a hurry that day,

418
00:18:54,759 --> 00:18:56,239
I didn't finish talking.

419
00:18:56,239 --> 00:18:58,120
The baby can have surgery
at three months old.

420
00:19:00,479 --> 00:19:01,559
So surgery is possible.

421
00:19:02,039 --> 00:19:04,120
Which means it can be treated.

422
00:19:05,319 --> 00:19:06,920
But surgery requires general anesthesia.

423
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,519
There's still risk.

424
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:09,960
Zhixia, I know.

425
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:13,239
I know it's scary, and it's unfair.

426
00:19:13,799 --> 00:19:16,079
But I can't make the decision for you.

427
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:18,719
Don't worry.

428
00:19:18,719 --> 00:19:20,719
The money from
the demolition of my old house

429
00:19:20,719 --> 00:19:23,160
will be used for the baby's treatment.

430
00:19:27,319 --> 00:19:27,920
Mom…

431
00:19:29,340 --> 00:19:30,960
Don't you want to
know the baby's gender?

432
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:32,719
A boy or a girl, it's the same.

433
00:19:34,130 --> 00:19:35,479
They're all flowers of the nation.

434
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:39,880
Why did you ask me to check before?

435
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:43,799
In my heart…

436
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:45,999
I just…

437
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:48,759
I was asking too much of you.

438
00:19:48,759 --> 00:19:49,759
Let me translate that.

439
00:19:49,759 --> 00:19:50,559
I understood.

440
00:19:52,559 --> 00:19:54,960
Since I already had a granddaughter,

441
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:57,319
I thought it might be nice
to have a grandson, too.

442
00:19:57,319 --> 00:19:58,479
That's all it was.

443
00:19:59,319 --> 00:19:59,960
Right?

444
00:20:00,039 --> 00:20:01,960
But now, Zhixia...

445
00:20:02,160 --> 00:20:02,719
I...

446
00:20:02,719 --> 00:20:04,920
As long as the baby's whole and healthy,

447
00:20:04,920 --> 00:20:06,960
that alone makes us lucky.

448
00:20:10,039 --> 00:20:10,719
Grandma.

449
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:17,519
Which half tastes better?

450
00:20:26,799 --> 00:20:27,519
They're both good.

451
00:20:27,799 --> 00:20:30,160
Yes, because they're from the same bun.

452
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:31,719
They taste just as good.

453
00:20:32,039 --> 00:20:33,670
Doesn't matter if it's a boy or a girl,

454
00:20:33,719 --> 00:20:35,479
or five fingers or six.

455
00:20:35,479 --> 00:20:36,239
No need to worry.

456
00:20:36,719 --> 00:20:37,319
Because we are

457
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:39,519
Mom and Dad's favorite babies.

458
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:42,440
Listen to her.

459
00:20:42,440 --> 00:20:43,719
Jiao's got real talent.

460
00:20:44,239 --> 00:20:44,920
Why can't you do

461
00:20:44,920 --> 00:20:46,039
just as well with essays?

462
00:20:46,039 --> 00:20:46,559
You know that?

463
00:20:46,559 --> 00:20:47,559
You're so annoying.

464
00:20:47,559 --> 00:20:49,479
She said it so well.
What's your problem?

465
00:20:54,479 --> 00:20:55,079
Mom…

466
00:20:57,160 --> 00:20:59,680
I had a bad attitude toward you before.

467
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:00,640
Please don't be mad.

468
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:01,239
No.

469
00:21:02,640 --> 00:21:04,519
I thought it was my fault.

470
00:21:05,319 --> 00:21:06,600
So first,

471
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:10,039
I want to reflect on my mistakes.

472
00:21:10,039 --> 00:21:11,600
Mom, um…

473
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:15,050
Let me just criticize myself first.

474
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:19,239
I was...

475
00:21:21,079 --> 00:21:23,200
I was way too picky about Zhang Hao.

476
00:21:23,660 --> 00:21:25,519
I kept pushing him
to get a director position.

477
00:21:26,079 --> 00:21:27,519
I was just passing on my anxiety.

478
00:21:27,999 --> 00:21:30,680
I was scared he'd fall behind his peers.

479
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:35,120
But later I calmed down.

480
00:21:36,360 --> 00:21:38,079
I'm a writer myself.

481
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:39,999
How did I let myself get pushed

482
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:43,079
into this mental trap?

483
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:46,559
It's not like I can't earn money.

484
00:21:46,960 --> 00:21:49,559
Zhang Hao's job allows him
to better care for his family.

485
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:50,960
That's why this home

486
00:21:51,719 --> 00:21:52,920
is so stable.

487
00:21:53,479 --> 00:21:54,319
So happy.

488
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,840
People spend their whole lives

489
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:01,079
looking for their own strength.

490
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:04,960
Not losing your joy and confidence

491
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:06,239
is the greatest success.

492
00:22:07,799 --> 00:22:09,559
Life is yours to live.

493
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:11,559
Other people, other things,

494
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,719
are just here to help.

495
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:15,160
If we have them,

496
00:22:16,600 --> 00:22:17,759
everyone's happy.

497
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:18,840
If not,

498
00:22:19,079 --> 00:22:21,200
we should take it in stride.

499
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:22,600
Right?

500
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:24,920
So Hao,

501
00:22:25,559 --> 00:22:27,999
live according to your own heart.

502
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:29,079
As for me,

503
00:22:29,999 --> 00:22:33,400
I need to find my own rhythm again.

504
00:22:37,840 --> 00:22:39,120
Is this still my wife?

505
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:41,960
Mom?

506
00:22:42,999 --> 00:22:44,360
Is this still my mom?

507
00:22:44,759 --> 00:22:46,160
Is this still my daughter?

508
00:22:46,960 --> 00:22:47,999
You guys are...

509
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:50,960
You're so familiar,
yet also feel like a stranger.

510
00:22:50,960 --> 00:22:52,700
Come on,
shouldn't you have grown up a bit?

511
00:22:54,319 --> 00:22:55,799
I've grown plenty.

512
00:23:01,799 --> 00:23:02,360
Eat up.

513
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:03,519
Eat up.

514
00:23:03,519 --> 00:23:04,999
All this was made with hard work.

515
00:23:06,719 --> 00:23:08,200
Eat. Have the bun.

516
00:23:08,200 --> 00:23:09,200
Which one's better?

517
00:23:10,079 --> 00:23:10,880
Which one's better?

518
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:13,640
It's sticking to my teeth.

519
00:23:19,840 --> 00:23:20,400
Hello.

520
00:23:20,719 --> 00:23:21,999
Have you made a decision?

521
00:23:23,519 --> 00:23:24,079
Hello.

522
00:23:24,079 --> 00:23:25,440
I'm Zhou Sha,

523
00:23:25,440 --> 00:23:26,559
COO of Manting Hotel Group.

524
00:23:27,519 --> 00:23:28,200
Hello.

525
00:23:28,920 --> 00:23:29,960
Don't you remember me?

526
00:23:30,039 --> 00:23:31,079
Of course I remember.

527
00:23:31,079 --> 00:23:32,960
Weren't you here
to book an engagement banquet?

528
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:34,600
I'm really sorry.

529
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:35,600
We lied to you last time.

530
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:38,610
We were actually representing the group
to do a detailed review

531
00:23:38,610 --> 00:23:40,160
of the catering operations you manage.

532
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:41,960
I've brought my team

533
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:43,999
to talk with you about future plans.

534
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:46,920
Okay, let's sit down and talk.

535
00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:47,360
Okay.

536
00:23:49,200 --> 00:23:50,079
Here, have some water.

537
00:23:50,640 --> 00:23:51,120
Thanks.

538
00:23:52,799 --> 00:23:53,279
Here.

539
00:23:55,319 --> 00:23:57,039
You want to talk partnership?

540
00:23:57,239 --> 00:23:57,880
That's right.

541
00:23:58,600 --> 00:24:00,039
Manting has already begun

542
00:24:00,039 --> 00:24:01,920
detailed talks with Nanxi Hotel

543
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:03,160
about other businesses.

544
00:24:03,160 --> 00:24:04,559
Now we just need your part.

545
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:08,319
We're looking to acquire
Nanxi's F&B division.

546
00:24:09,279 --> 00:24:09,880
Acquire?

547
00:24:10,559 --> 00:24:11,120
Yes.

548
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:15,279
Rather than "acquire,"

549
00:24:15,410 --> 00:24:16,600
think of it as a partnership.

550
00:24:17,279 --> 00:24:17,960
Miss Shen,

551
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:19,400
may I walk you through

552
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:20,519
our plans for Nanxi Hotel

553
00:24:20,519 --> 00:24:22,319
after it folds

554
00:24:22,319 --> 00:24:23,039
into Manting?

555
00:24:24,519 --> 00:24:25,400
Here's the proposal.

556
00:24:28,680 --> 00:24:30,559
The Old Town is surrounded
by heritage streets.

557
00:24:30,880 --> 00:24:32,999
Manting plans
to respect the local style,

558
00:24:33,200 --> 00:24:35,360
while building on
our high-end custom standards,

559
00:24:35,360 --> 00:24:37,319
and creating for our guests

560
00:24:37,319 --> 00:24:39,440
a unique immersive travel experience.

561
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:41,479
It's all within
2 kilometers of the hotel,

562
00:24:41,479 --> 00:24:43,920
both inside
and outside the hotel grounds.

563
00:24:44,759 --> 00:24:46,120
So our restaurant here

564
00:24:46,120 --> 00:24:48,120
is part of your bigger plan?

565
00:24:48,559 --> 00:24:49,160
Exactly.

566
00:24:49,440 --> 00:24:51,840
Our group will
invest heavily to rebuild it.

567
00:24:53,440 --> 00:24:55,079
And don't worry about the cost.

568
00:24:55,079 --> 00:24:56,559
Everything you've put in before

569
00:24:56,559 --> 00:24:57,759
will be fully covered.

570
00:24:58,239 --> 00:24:59,120
You'll only get more.

571
00:25:01,239 --> 00:25:03,410
Honestly, the last time we talked,

572
00:25:03,410 --> 00:25:05,279
and when you walked me
through your proposal,

